# GitHub sync

When the user asks to update GitHub, keep GitHub updated, publish changes, or sync the repo:

1. After finishing code/docs/script changes, commit and push to `origin/main` at `https://github.com/Soham11k/GlobeCloud.git`.
2. Use `./scripts/publish-github.sh` or follow the git safety protocol: never commit `.env`, `.env.deploy`, or secrets.
3. Write a concise commit message focused on why the change was made.
4. Confirm the commit hash and repo URL in the response.

If there are no changes to commit, say the repo is already up to date.
